# 2. 足りない何か

Haruka: ...
Saito: Alright, let's summarize what we've come up with so far.
Airi: First, we've got spreading hope to others and increasing our media exposure.
Minori: We also have, umm... Whether or not we can appear as a group! That's really important!
Haruka: Right. A lot of people will be hearing about MORE MORE JUMP! for the very first time, so we'll want their first impression of us to be that we're a proper idol group.
Shizuku: Then there was the matter of leaving enough time for us to keep doing streams.
Shizuku: We've already had to reduce the number we do, so I fear that our fans are going to feel just that much more disappointed if we go any further...
Airi: I mean, spreading hope to others through our streams has always been a big deal to us, so we should keep trying to do as many as we can.
Saito: What else is there...?
Haruka: (I think we've covered just about everything...)
Haruka: (But...)
Minori: But are there any offers that actually cover all those points?
Airi: I doubt there are going to be any that cover all of them, so we might want to order them by importance.
Airi: With spreading hope to others for sure taking the top spot...
Airi: Followed by increasing our media exposure. Doing those two things will be the quickest way for us to realize our dream.
Shizuku: Yes, I agree with that order.
Saito: Understood. Then, I'll place those two things at the forefront, while also taking the other criteria we've come up with into consideration...
Haruka: ...
Saito: Is something wrong, Haruka?
Haruka: Sorry, but... Would it be alright if I gave this some more thought?
Airi: Huh...?
Haruka: I agree with what you said in terms of those two things taking top priority, Airi. I don't see anything wrong with that ordering.
Haruka: But...
Haruka: I feel like we're still missing something.
Minori: We are?
Haruka: Yeah... I'm not sure how to put it into words...
Haruka: But when I ask myself if choosing work like this will really lead to us making our dream come true, I feel like we're still missing some key piece...
Airi: A key piece...
Haruka: Sorry. I know what I'm saying is really vague...
Haruka: And I know I have a habit of overthinking things in these sorts of situations.
Airi: What are you talking about? Your attentiveness has saved our skins a bunch of times already!
Shizuku: She's right. If there's something on your mind, Haruka, then I'd also like to think about it with you.
Shizuku: So, let's take our time and try to come up with a solution that we can all agree on.
Minori: Yeah, I'm sure we'll be able to figure out what we're missing if we all put our heads together!
Haruka: Thank you all...
Haruka: That being said, we shouldn't keep these people waiting too long. We'll need to set ourselves a deadline, and then decide which offers to accept...
Haruka: So, let's give ourselves until tomorrow. I promise to have my answer by then.
Airi: Sounds good. We'll also take another hard look at things!
Saito: For now, let's adjourn this meeting... You all have that magazine interview scheduled, so let's start getting ready to head over!
Minori: What?! It's already that late?! L-Lemme go get my notebook! It has all my answers to their questions in it!
Shizuku: Oh, didn't you just put it back in your bag?
Minori: *Gasp* Y-You're right...!
Airi: Geez, relax, will you?
Haruka: I still can't figure it out...
Airi: With spreading hope to others for sure taking the top spot...
Airi: Followed by increasing our media exposure. Doing those two things will be the quickest way for us to realize our dream.
Haruka: (I still don't think what Airi said is wrong.)
Haruka: (But...)
Haruka: (Is it really okay for us to make decisions based on just these criteria?)
Haruka: (Will we be able to stand there? Will our fans be able to come see us...?)
Haruka: (On that stage...)
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: (Come to think of it, what criteria did we use as ASRUN when it came to work?)
Haruka: (Mr. Hiiragi always...)
